== History ==
; Kotohira Shrine
In {{ill|1859|en|1859|qid=Q7687|lt=1859|1=1859}} ({{ill|Ansei 6|ja|安政6年|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ansei 6|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}), with the opening of {{ill|Port of Yokohama|en|Port of Yokohama|qid=Q1190021|lt=Yokohama Port|1=Port of Yokohama}}, the proprietor of the Iwakame Rō brothel in the {{ill|Minatozaki Yūkaku|ja|港崎遊郭|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minatozaki Yūkaku|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 港崎遊廓|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 港崎遊廓|1=Miyozaki Quarter|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11563079}}, Sakichi of Iwatsukiya, enshrined the {{ill|Zōzu-san Konpira Daigongen|ja|象頭山 金毘羅大権現|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zōzu-san Konpira Daigongen|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} from {{ill|Sanuki Province|en|Sanuki Province|qid=Q929682|lt=Sanuki Province|1=Sanuki Province}}. The shrine was initially established in the {{ill|Minatozaki Town|ja|港崎町|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minatozaki Town|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} area (the current site of {{ill|Yokohama Park|ja|横浜公園|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokohama Park|1=Yokohama Park|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11542924}}).<br>
In {{ill|1872|en|1872|qid=Q7753|lt=1872|1=1872}} ({{ill|1872|en|1872|qid=Q7753|lt=Meiji 5|1=1872}}), along with the relocation of the {{ill|Yūkaku|en|Yūkaku|qid=Q1060846|lt=Yūkaku|1=Yūkaku}}, the shrine was moved to the coastal area of Takashima Town 7-chōme and renamed Kotohira Shrine. In {{ill|1882|en|1882|qid=Q7812|lt=1882|1=1882}} ({{ill|1882|en|1882|qid=Q7812|lt=Meiji 15|1=1882}}), it was relocated again to {{ill|Magane Town|ja|真金町|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Magane Town|1=Maganechō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11583588}} for the same reasons.<br>
The shrine was damaged during both the {{ill|1923 Great Kantō Earthquake|ja|関東大震災|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1923 Great Kantō Earthquake|1=aftermath of 1923 Great Kantō earthquake|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q3742341}} on September 1, {{ill|1923|en|1923|qid=Q2169|lt=1923|1=1923}} ({{ill|1923|en|1923|qid=Q2169|lt=Taisho 11|1=1923}}) and the {{ill|Yokohama Air Raid|ja|横浜大空襲|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokohama Air Raid|1=Bombing of Yokohama|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11542960}} on May 29, {{ill|1945|en|1945|qid=Q5240|lt=1945|1=1945}} ({{ill|1945|en|1945|qid=Q5240|lt=Showa 20|1=1945}}). Although it was rebuilt each time, the current main shrine building was reconstructed in {{ill|1988|en|1988|qid=Q2426|lt=1988|1=1988}} ({{ill|1988|en|1988|qid=Q2426|lt=Showa 63|1=1988}}).

; Ōtori Shrine
In {{ill|1872|en|1872|qid=Q7753|lt=1872|1=1872}} ({{ill|1872|en|1872|qid=Q7753|lt=Meiji 5|1=1872}}), when the {{ill|Minatozaki Yūkaku|ja|港崎遊郭|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minatozaki Yūkaku|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 港崎遊廓|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 港崎遊廓|1=Miyozaki Quarter|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11563079}} was moved to Takashima Town, a deity known as the "Otorisama" was enshrined following the example of {{ill|Yoshiwara Yūkaku|ja|吉原|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshiwara Yūkaku|1=Yoshihara|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q4053786}} in {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokyo|1=Tokyo Proper|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q7473516}}.<ref>It is unclear whether this refers to {{ill|Ōtori Shrine (Taitō)|ja|鷲神社 (台東区)|1=Ōtori Shrine (Taito Ward)|lt=Ōtori Shrine|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtori Shrine (Taitō)|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtori Shrine (Taito Ward)|qq=}} in Asakusa, Tokyo, or {{ill|Ōtori Shrine (Adachi Ward)|lt=Ōtori Shrine (Adachi Ward)|lt=Ōtori Shrine (Adachi)|ja|大鷲神社 (足立区)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtori Shrine (Adachi)|qq=}} in Hanahata, Adachi, Tokyo.</ref> From this time, the {{ill|Tori no Ichi|ja|酉の市|1=Tori-no-Ichi|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tori no Ichi|13=User:Immanuelle/Tori-no-Ichi|qq=}} festival was held, similar to Asakusa. Initially, it was a subordinate shrine within the grounds, but it is now enshrined alongside Kotohira Shrine.

== location ==
* 1-3 Magane Town, Minami-ku, Yokohama, Kanagawa Prefecture, Japan

